snippet.textDisplay:
I am so lucky I’m poor, because I don’t think I’d be able to ever fully appreciate being rich (at least in this hotel):
* I really don’t like the gaudy over-the-top style
* I don’t like how I would feel like I can’t touch anything, because I could break something
* I don’t like how much wasted space is being used for random rooms (that most people probably would only use them to walk through to the next room)
* I don’t like how there is no kitchen, so you’re being forced to either get room service or go out to eat (I like the wholesomeness of a home cooked meal)
